                 Philadelphia Mayor's Action Center

                 Mission
                 The Mayor's Action Center is the Information and Complaint Office for
   the City of Philadelphia.  It is staffed by a Director of Service
   Representatives, and a number of part-time employees who are pleased to
   serve you.

   Please feel free to contact our staff if you have any City government
   service requests for problem-solving or information.  When you call,
   please provide your name, address, and telephone number for a quick
   response.

   Contact Information
       Renee Grundy, Executive Director
       The Mayor's Action Center
       City Hall, Room 143
       Philadelphia, PA 19107
       (215) 686-3000; (215) 686-2250
       Office Hours: Monday - Friday, 9:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.
